{"body": "I'm :-1: on this one. As described above it will only track methods defined with `scope` but class methods\r\nare an equal way to achieve the same behavior.\r\n\r\nI don't think your use-case is a good example either. Relying on the defined scopes to restrict the callable methods\r\nseems bad. I'd go with an explicit whitelist:\r\n\r\n```ruby\r\ndef allowed_scopes\r\n  [:latest, :archived]\r\nend\r\n```", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/21308559", "created_at": "2013-07-21T11:20:33Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/11503#issuecomment-21308559", "updated_at": "2013-07-21T11:20:33Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 11503, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/senny/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/senny/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/senny/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/senny", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/senny/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/senny", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/senny/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/3d698e2872c07061a455d9e250861235?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fd1359f9934ee5a75ed441ffce412a0a1.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/senny/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/senny/received_events", "gravatar_id": "3d698e2872c07061a455d9e250861235", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/senny/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "senny", "type": "User", "id": 5402, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/senny/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5237d3babd3543c151007fda"}, "id": 21308559, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/11503"}
